Site.Name: "VERNON FORK MUSCATATUCK RIVER AT VERNON, IN"

SiteVisit.WeatherDescription: clear, warm, no precip, calm winds
SiteVisit.Comment: Site had not been visited in some time due to slipping through the cracks on the IN/KY handoff. Forgot to download data. N2 had run out. Replaced the tank at 0900 with a small tank. Decided to make a couple QMs.

StreamFlowControlInspection.Comment: Rock/gravel/dirt riffle in wide U shape facing upstream. The level was about even with the second channel on the right side that is covered in thick grass and some sapplings. Flow had been up in the section recently. Both banks heavy trees and brush.

DischargeMeasurement.Comment: Set aquaclac to EDT. Moved 1 hour back in SVMOBILE. Used MGH as decrease was <.10' and evenly distributed. Did not use the 932 reading as the last sections for this time had little flow.
